-- Foreigners Sold C$6.31 Billion of Canada Securities in February
-- B y   G r e g   Q u i n n
-- 2013-04-16T12:30:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-16/foreigners-sold-c-6-31-billion-of-canada-securities-in-february.html
Foreigners sold a net C$6.31 billion ($6.18 billion) of Canadian securities in February, led by the biggest sale of stocks since October 2007, government figures showed.  Investors abroad sold a net C$11.56 billion of Canadian equities,  Statistics Canada  said today from Ottawa. Most of that total came from mergers and acquisitions that involved the purchase of Canadian companies, Statistics Canada said.  Foreign investors in February also bought C$5.25 billion of Canadian debt instruments, with a net C$8.01 billion purchase of bonds partly offset by a C$2.76 billion divestment of money market paper.  Canadians  bought  a net C$4.40 billion of foreign securities in February, including C$4.05 billion of debt and C$351 million of equities.  To contact the reporter on this story: Greg Quinn in Ottawa at  gquinn1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editors responsible for this story: Christopher Wellisz at  cwellisz@bloomberg.net ;  David Scanlan  at  dscanlan@bloomberg.net . 